body:
Before this fix, the following code
```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod test {
    use crate::PropertyTypeRegistration;

    #[test]
    fn test_property_type_registration() {
        type Map = std::collections::HashMap<u32, f64>;

        assert_eq!(PropertyTypeRegistration::of::<Map>().short_name, "HashMap<u32, f64>");
        assert_eq!(PropertyTypeRegistration::of::<Option<Map>>().short_name, "Option<HashMap<u32, f64>>");
    }
}
```
panicked during the evaluation of the second assert with the message "should end with closing carrot". This is caused by the `PropertyTypeRegistration::get_short_name` function which was not designed to handle nested generics. This PR fixes this. It is a complete rewrite of the function which steps linearly through the type name to avoid having to build some tree structure to parse the nested generics. I also added some tests for this.

Allows to create color from hex value

```rust
// RGB
Color::hex("FFF").unwrap() == Color::rgb(1.0, 1.0, 1.0)
// RGBA
Color::hex("FFFF").unwrap() == Color::rgba(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0)
// RRGGBB
Color::hex("FFFFFF").unwrap() == Color::rgb(1.0, 1.0, 1.0)
// RRGGBBAA
Color::hex("FFFFFFFF").unwrap() == Color::rgba(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0)
```
